headline: Is Hormel Foods (HRL) Attractive After A 39% Three Year Share Price Decline?
summary: If you are wondering whether Hormel Foods is a bargain or a value trap at its recent price of US$24.43, it helps to slow down and look at what the numbers are really saying about the stock. The share price has inched up about 1.3% over the last month and is up 4.4% year to date, yet it still reflects a 15.9% decline over the last year and a 39.0% and 43.5% decline over the last 3 and 5 years. headline: What to Expect From Hormel Foods’ Next Quarterly Earnings Report
summary: Hormel Foods is expected to report its first-quarter results soon, and analysts are projecting a single-digit year-over-year drop in earnings.
